✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: this is pretty simple but ok for a CoC

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Perfect CoC puzzle. Ideal for developers that want fun.

❌ Rejected the contribution.
Comment: Why do you all like this type of CoC on this site? It's just an 5 line implementation, nothing spectacular, not even new.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Nice visual application, perfectly timed for a clash of code.

Nice clash! You currently have 8 different cases, which is nice - but half of those will be validator. So, during the clash players will test according to example, odd width/even heigh, both even, and one square, while the validators are then different cases. Validators should reflect their respective test cases. It seems you have distinguished 8 really different cases, so you might want to double the total: your current cases all as test cases, and then very similar cases as validator cases.

Your contribution has been uploaded twice. Please remove one. The other link is:
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/523214de8bd6cbc7e33f271de81ad5f298059

Thanks.
Deleted. It come from a networks issue. Thanks,
Thanks, I update tests. Validators now look like the original test.
Thank you, Remember to upvote if you think it deserves it.

First test and first validator
* Please change "Exemple" to "Example".

* Please revise the pair so that they are slightly different and not the same.

Thanks.

Thank you. My comments on the contribution itself:

Goal section
* Please change "w horizontal squaresand h vertical squares" to "[[h]] rows of [[w]] squares per row".

* Please change "case" to "corner".

* Please change "a white squares" to "a white square".

* Please remove the example as it has already been shown in Example section.

Input section
* Line 1: Please add "Two integers for" before "width".

Output section
* Please delete "Next".

* Please format "h lines" in <<bold>>.

Stub generator
* Please fix the typo: "Les't" to "Let's".

Cases
* 3 of the cases: Please do not use non-ASCII characters because the console cannot show any error messages properly, e.g. the console cannot show "♥ ♦" properly for "One case" Test:

Failure
Found: #.#.#.
Expected: \-30\-103\-91

This will make debugging difficult for a clash player.

Thanks.
